# Refactor Rules for sfxClanker

When refactoring sfxClanker.py:
- Always import from utils/ instead of duplicating code.
- Use SFXLibrary from utils.sfx_library, not inline.
- Use build_search_query and enhance_query from utils.query_builder.
- Use process_audio and preview_audio from utils.audio_processor.
- Add type hints to all functions and methods (e.g., def func(arg: str) -> bool).
- Use TypedDict for item dicts if needed.
- Keep main under 250 lines by extracting to utils.
- Run pytest and mypy after changes to ensure no regressions.
- Do not modify prompts.json or .clinerules/helloknight_sfx_library.mdc.

Refactor goals: modularity, testability, type safety.

# Git Rules for Refactoring
- Before refactoring: git status, git pull origin main
- After refactoring: pytest tests/, mypy ., git add ., git commit -m "Refactor: description", git push origin main
